      "title": "Sri Lanka raises Rs17.5bn from after auction Treasuries sales",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka has raised 17.5 billion rupees from sales of Treasury bills at weighted average yields after the initial auction on Wednesday, the debt office said.",
        "The debt said there were subscriptions for 20.2 billion rupees.",
        "The weighted average yields were 28.08 percent, 28.74 percent and 28.11 percent for 3, 6 and 12 month bills at the auction.",
        "Foreign exchange and fuel shortages emerge when the central bank buys Treasury bills for new money and not the public. (Colombo/July08/2022)"
      ],
